{
  "doc_id": "56705",
  "text": "Chlorophyll was extracted by boiling the leaves in 95% ethanol at 80 °C. The chlorophyll concentration per unit fresh weight of leaf was calculated as described by Lichtenthaler [CITATION_1] . The content was determined spectrophotometrically using the formula Chl (a+b)=5.24 A 664.2 +22.24 A 648.6 and chlorophyll content (%)=Chl (a+b)×V×10 -3 /m, where Chl (a+b) is the chlorophyll concentration in μg ml -1 , A is absorption at the indicated wavelength, V is the volume of the 95% ethanol, and m is the mass of the leaves.",
